Ali Sethi (Urdu/Punjabi: علی سیٹھی‎; /seɪtiː/; born July 2, 1984) is a Pakistani singer, musician, writer, and columnist.[1] Sethi was globally recognized for writing the book, The Wish Maker. The book was short-listed for DSC Prize for South Asian Literature and the Shakti Bhatt First Book Prize Award. Sethi has written several columns for New York Times, The New Yorker, The Caravan, and The Friday Times.[2]
